title: Travis Barker will sign his new memoir in Orange County
text: Travis Barker will sign his new memoir in Orange County Oct. 20, 2015 Updated 12:00 a.m. 1 of 21 Blink-182 drummer Travis Barker will sign his new memoir, “Can I Say: Living Large, Cheating Death, and Drums, Drums, Drums,” on Friday at Barnes & Noble in Huntington Beach. LEONARD ORTIZ, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER 1 of 21 Blink-182 drummer Travis Barker will sign his new memoir, “Can I Say: Living Large, Cheating Death, and Drums, Drums, Drums,” on Friday at Barnes & Noble in Huntington Beach. The plane had crashed moments after takeoff; Barker and Goldstein were the only two survivors. DJ AM, whose real name was Adam Goldstein, died of a drug overdose on Aug. 28, less than a year after surviving the plane crash.
